{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 22:12:54.509633", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission recorded.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [host_2_1_1_1]\n- root_cause_name: [host_static_blackhole]\n\nRecommended immediate remediation (not required for submission):\n- On host_2_1_1_1 remove the permanent ARP/neighbor entry for 10.2.1.1 and allow normal ARP resolution:\n  - Example (Linux): ip neigh del 10.2.1.1 dev eth0\n  - Then verify: ip neigh show 10.2.1.1 && ping -c 3 10.2.1.1\n- If the entry reappears, inspect host startup scripts, network manager config, or any static neighbor configuration for why a permanent ARP was added and remove/fix it.\n- Optionally, reboot the host or restart its networking service after correcting the config.\n\nIf you want, I can provide exact commands for the host OS present, draft a remediation playbook, or help craft a monitoring/alert to detect reappearance of permanent ARP entries.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2226, "output_tokens": 231, "total_tokens": 2457, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
